NO-BAKE CHOCOLATE PEANUT BUTTER CARAMEL BARS 🍫🥜

Healthy enough to be breakfast, tasty enough to be dessert - these chocolate peanut butter caramel bars are to die for you guys. They’re also incredibly easy to make and topped with delicious @purely_elizabeth chocolate sea salt probiotic granola for the perfect sweet and salty crunch on these chewy gooey bars. Grab the full gluten-free, vegan, refined sugar-free recipe below and head over to @purely_elizabeth and click the link in bio to shop all of their gluten free granolas!

No-Bake Chocolate Peanut Butter Caramel Bars
MAKES 20 BARS

Chocolate Brownie Base

1 cup raw cashews
1 1/4 cup gluten free rolled oats
1/3 cup unsweetened raw cacao powder
1/2 cup maple syrup
1/3 cup coconut flour
2 tbsp natural creamy peanut butter
1/2 tsp salt
1-2 tbsp water (if needed)

Peanut Butter Caramel Layer

1 cup soft, pitted medjool dates
1/2 cup natural creamy peanut butter
1 tsp vanilla extract
1/4 cup warm water
1/4 tsp of salt

Chocolate Sea Salt Topping

2 cups @purely_elizabeth chocolate sea salt probiotic granola

Line a 9x9 metal brownie pan with parchment paper. Set aside.

Add all ingredients for the brownie base except water to a food processor and mix on high speed until completely combined and a slightly crumbly mixture is formed. If the mixture feels too dry, add 1 tbsp of water at a time until it binds together when pressed between your fingers. Pour into the pan and use a rubber spatula to press into an even layer.

Rinse out the food processor and add all ingredients for the peanut butter date caramel. Blend on high until totally smooth. Pour on top of the brownie layer and use the spatula to evenly coat.

Sprinkle with the granola and gently press down using clean hands or the rubber spatula. Transfer to the freezer and chill for at least 1 hour before cutting into bars. Store in the freezer (my favorite) or the fridge and enjoy right away, frozen or chilled!

Decadent and rich flavors are not lacking in this Chocolate Peanut Butter Tart. ✨ @danishealthyeats used our Vanilla Chocolate Chip Granola for the perfect crunchy tart crust layer and combined it with a creamy chocolate peanut butter layer for a dessert you won’t feel bad indulging in. Recipe below and tap the link in bio to shop our Granola.

Crust:
2 cups Vanilla Chocolate Chip Granola
1/3 cup coconut oil, melted

Filling:
1 cup Peanut Butter
1 cup canned coconut milk, shaken
1/3 cup maple syrup
1/4 cup coconut oil or cacao butter, melted
1 tsp vanilla
Pinch of sea salt

Topping:
1 cup chocolate chips
1 tbsp canned coconut milk

Instructions:
Add the granola and coconut oil to a food processor, processing until fine crumbles form.
Line a cake pan with parchment paper and press the crumbles into the pan. Set aside.
Make the filling by adding all of the ingredients to a blender, blending until super smooth and creamy. Pour over the base.
Add the chocolate chips and coconut milk to a heat-proof bowl and microwave in 30 second increments, stirring between each one, until thick and smooth. Pour over the peanut butter filling and spread out the best you can.
Top with chocolate chips and more crushed granola if you’re feeing fancy.
Place in the freezer to set, at least 2 hours, before cutting into pieces.

Note: Let thaw 10 mins before enjoying for best texture! Store in freezer.

Did you know you can use oats to make flour? @figandoliveplatter used our Original Superfood Oats to make this delicious Citrus Olive Oil Cake to sneak in some nourishing ingredients to your dessert. Head over to the link in bio to shop our Oats and get the recipe below.

Ingredients:
2 eggs
1/3 cup olive oil
1/4 cup orange juice, freshly squeezed
1 cup & 1 tbsp of Purely Elizabeth Super Food Flour
(* see instructions on how to make the
flour
1 &1/2 tsps. of baking powder
Zest 1 large orange
½ tsp vanilla extract, optional
½ tsp baking soda
Pinch of salt
½ cup coconut sugar, adjust sweetness to your liking

Directions:
Preheat oven to 350F
In a blender, add about 1 &1/4 cup of Superfood Original Oats. Blend until mixture is fine. Sift the flour through a sieve. This is a very important step and if you have difficulty sifting the flour quickly, use a spoon to assist. Tip: Feel free to pour the mixture back into the blender and give it another blend to make sure it is very fine.
In a large bowl, add the sugar and orange zest. Using clean fingers, rub the zest and sugar together. This method releases essential oil from the orange zest into the sugar and gives a
flavor-packed cake.
Now add the eggs into the sugar and whisk for about 30-45 seconds.
Add the olive oil, orange juice and mix well.
In another bowl, whisk together the flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt together to combine.
Add the dry ingredients into the wet ingredients and mix until the batter is smooth and lump free.
Pour the batter into a
9-inch round cake pan that is greased and lined with parchment paper. Tip: Add parchment around the edges of the pan as
well to ensure that the cake releases seamlessly.
Place the pan in the oven on the middle rack and bake for 26-28 minutes (uninterrupted)
When a toothpick inserted into the center of the cake comes out clean, it is ready.
Place the pan on a rack to cool for 10 minutes.
Run a knife around the edge of the pan, and carefully invert the cake onto a plate. Remove
the parchment and let the cake rest on the rack until it is cool.
Once cooled, decorate the cake with a dusting of powdered sugar and thinly sliced orange peel

Ingredients:⁠
✨1 stick butter (115g)⁠
✨1/3 cup light brown sugar (65g)⁠

✨1 egg⁠
✨1/4 tsp baking powder⁠

Ingredients:
Crust:
- 1 bag Chocolate Sea Salt Granola
- 1/4 cup coconut oil, melted

Cheesecake filling:
- 8 oz Cream cheese, softened(can use dairy free)
- 1 tablespoon honey
-1 tsp vanilla

Instructions:

These Double Blueberry Oatmeal Muffins by @broccyourbody are made with our Original Superfood Oatmeal and make the perfect addition to your brunch festivities. Ingredients:⁠
1/2 cup Original Superfood Oats⁠
1/2 cup water ⁠
1 1/2 cups all purpose flour ⁠
1 tsp baking powder ⁠
1/2 tsp baking soda⁠
1/2 tsp kosher salt⁠
1/2 cup butter or coconut oil, melted ⁠
1/2 cup sugar ⁠
1/2 tsp vanilla extract ⁠
1 egg ⁠
2 cups blueberries ⁠
Crumble to top:⁠
1/4 cup brown sugar ⁠
2 tbsp cold butter, cut into small cubes ⁠
2 tbsp all purpose flour ⁠
2 tbsp Original Superfood Oats⁠
⁠
Instructions:⁠
Preheat the oven to 400F and line or grease a muffin tin.⁠
Make the crumble by combining all ingredients in a small bowl with your hands. Set aside.⁠
In a small bowl, combine the oats and water and let it sit for 5-10 minutes. In a mixing bowl, whisk together the butter or oil, sugar, vanilla and egg until completely combined. Stir in the oats. In another bowl, combine the flour, baking powder, baking soda, and salt. Stir the dry mixture into the wet mixture until just combined, then fold in blueberries. Add 2-3 tablespoons of batter to each muffin tin, keeping in mind they will rise a bit. Top with the crumble and bake for 20-24 minutes or until the muffins start to turn golden brown and the center is cooked through. Makes 12 muffins.⁠

No need to turn on the oven for this delicious recipe by @broccyourbody. These Chocolate & PB No-Bake Oatmeal Bars are a perfect breakfast on-the-go or snack idea. ⁠
Ingredients:⁠
Base:⁠
1 3/4 cup Purely Elizabeth Superfood Original Oats⁠
1/2 cup butter or coconut oil⁠
1/3 cup coconut sugar⁠
1/2 tsp vanilla extract⁠
1/4 tsp kosher salt ⁠

Filling:⁠
1 cup chocolate chips⁠
1 cup creamy peanut butter⁠
To top:⁠
1/2 cup Purely Elizabeth  Vanilla Chocolate Chip Granola⁠
Flaky sea salt⁠

1/3 cup peanut butter
1 tbsp honey
1/2 tsp cinnamon
1/2 cup chocolate chips
2 tsp coconut oil
1 cup Purely Elizabeth Honey Peanut Butter Superfood Cereal

Instructions:
Combine the peanut butter, honey and cinnamon together. Set aside.
Place a piece of parchment paper on a large plate.
Slice the banana into thin rounds. Place half of them on the parchment paper. Add a small dollop of the peanut butter mixture to each round, then add another banana slice on top. Freeze for 1 hour.
In a microwave at 50% powder or double broiler, melt the chocolate and coconut oil together, stirring every 15 seconds until melted and smooth. Crush the cereal and place in a shallow bowl.
Dip the frozen banana bite in the chocolate then coat with cereal. Freeze for another hour before eating.
Store them in a ziplock bag in the freezer for easy snacking! #easyrecipes #healthyrecipes #healthydessert #healthydessertrecipes

Cozy up on this chill morning with this Blueberry Baked Oatmeal from @chloescreativeeats! 🫐

Ingredients:
1 tbsp ground flaxseed
3 tbsp water
1/2 cup fresh blueberries
1/3 cup @purely_elizabeth Original Superfood Oats
1/2 tsp cinnamon
1/8 tsp salt
1/4 cup milk of choice
1 scoop vanilla protein powder
1 tbsp nut butter
1 tbsp maple syrup
1/2 tsp vanilla extract
1/2 tsp baking powder
Sprinkling of @purely_elizabeth Original Granola

Toppings:
Yogurt
Nut butter

Instructions:
1️⃣ Combine flaxseed + water to prepare flax egg. Set aside to let thicken.
2️⃣ Spray cooking spray in a small baking dish + preheat oven to 350F.
3️⃣ Add blueberries in a single layer on bottom of dish.
4️⃣ In a small bowl, combine oats, cinnamon + salt. Sprinkle mixture on top of blueberries.
5️⃣ In a small bowl, whisk milk, protein powder, nut butter, maple syrup, vanilla extract, baking powder + flax egg. Pour mixture over oats.
6️⃣ Top with granola + more blueberries. Bake for 40-45 minutes until cooked through.
7️⃣ Let cool, add toppings, + enjoy!
